Title: Verify "Forgot password?" link from Login page navigates to reset page

Preconditions:
- Application is accessible in a browser
- User is on the Login page (login.html)

Priority: High
Test Type: Functional / Navigation

Steps to reproduce:
1) Open the application home page (index.html).
2) From the navigation, click "Login" to open the login page.
3) On the login page, locate and click the "Forgot password?" link.

Expected Result:
- Browser navigates to the password reset page:
  - URL should be `.../forgot-password.html` (or equivalent correct path).
  - Page title should indicate password reset (e.g. “Reset Password”).
  - A form is displayed to request a reset (email field + submit button).

Actual Result:
- Browser attempts to open `.../forgot.html`.
- Page cannot be found (404) or displays an error.
- Password reset flow cannot be started from the login page.

Attachments(*imagine*):
- Screenshot of login page showing the incorrect link URL in the browser’s status bar.
- Screenshot of 404/error page after clicking the link.
